Name:                http-encodings
Version:             0.99
Synopsis: character and content encodings used in HTTP
Description: A library for encoding and decoding bodies of HTTP messages, designed to work with the HTTP and http-server libraries. WANTED: a library implementing Unix "compress" command encoding/decoding (or the LZW algorithm).
Homepage:            chudnov.com/git-public/http-encodings/
License:             BSD3
License-file:        LICENSE
Author:              Andrey Chudnov
Maintainer:          oss@chudnov.com
